From 6281827d9bb8b1d031e4281b42629077d7e2b34c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 17:28:16 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 3: PR data plane via gh CLI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Stand up KRT's GitHub data layer. All GitHub access funnels through a
single gh-CLI shell-out service in the main process; the renderer
binds to it via ProxyChannel.

- vs/platform/krt/common: PullRequest/Comment/Reviewer/CheckRun types,
  IGhClient + IPullRequestProvider decorators, typed KrtError surface
  for gh-missing / auth-expired / rate-limit / bad-url.
- vs/platform/krt/electron-main: GhClientMainService (detect once,
  spawn 'gh api' for JSON), PullRequestProviderMainService (parses
  GitHub PR URL, calls REST, maps to PullRequest).
- IPC: app.ts registers krt:gh and krt:pullRequest channels.
- vs/workbench/services/krt/electron-browser: thin ProxyChannel-based
  singletons for IGhClient + IPullRequestProvider.
- "KRT: Open PR" command (vs/workbench/contrib/krt/electron-browser):
  prompts for URL with recent-PR quick-pick, persists to IStorageService
  under krt.recentPRs, console.logs the parsed PullRequest. Friendly
  hints on KrtError; Phase 4 replaces these with the onboarding screen.

Demo gate: F1 → KRT: Open PR → paste cli/cli#1 → console shows
"interactive pr list" PR object end-to-end. Re-run shows recent-PR
quick-pick.

Reviewers / checks / comments fetching is deferred to Phase 5; Phase 3
ships only enough fields to prove the wiring.
